				<wikidot:authorName>OptimisticLucio</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3199573</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>While it was competently written, was funny, and was an overall an enjoyable read&#8230; I really cannot in good conscience bring myself to upvote this. It's <em>too</em> lolFoundation for my tastes, with some of the doctors even acting <em>more</em> irrationally than they did in the old lolFoundation stories, canonizing Jack's List..</p> <p>Also, none of the other &quot;Jacks&quot; actually felt like <em>the</em> Jack. They were just 'crazy random person,' and while Bright himself did have quirks and a personality in other lol stories, I didn't really see them shine in his clones. As far as I was concerned, it was just &quot;site-53 went crazy,&quot; not &quot;site-53 turned into Jack Bright.&quot;</p> <p>Final thing that bothered me was that this story seemed to have forgotten that one of Bright's main characteristics was &quot;wants desperately to die.&quot; There are points in the story where Bright is offered eternal freedom and&#8230; sounds <em>hurt</em> that someone would want to do that, when (usually) he's the first one to jump at the opportunity.</p> <p><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">also I browse the two main SCP subreddits a lot and I might have developed an deep-rooted dislike for lolFoundation Bright</span></p> <p>All in all, while it was well written, when looking back I really cannot say this was a good SCP. Sorry mate.</p> <p>-1.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
